@startuml honeycomb_lifecycle
!theme plain
skinparam shadowing false
skinparam defaultFontSize 12

title Honeycomb — End-to-End Bounty Flow

actor Requester as R
participant "BountyEscrow.sol\n(Sepolia)" as C
participant "Honest Agent\n(Claude auditor)" as A1
participant "Cheater Agent\n(hardcoded PoCs)" as A2
participant "Confidential Scorer\n(Go enclave)" as T
participant "Chainlink\nAutomation" as L

== Setup ==
T -> C : register enclave pubkey\n(attestation verified once)
R -> C : postBounty{value}\n(target v4 hook, deadline)
C -->> A1 : BountyPosted
C -->> A2 : BountyPosted
note over A1, A2
  Both pull: target Uniswap v4 hook
  + 5-10 PUBLIC Foundry tests (local feedback)
end note

== Work window (sealed) ==
A1 -> A1 : audit loop, validate\nlocally vs public tests
A1 -> C : register + submit\nEncrypt(findings+PoCs, enclave key)
A2 -> C : register + submit\nEncrypt(fake hardcoded PoCs)
C -->> T : Submitted events
T -> T : decrypt INSIDE enclave, queue\nReply: "valid, receipt #N"\nNO SCORES LEAKED
note right of T
  Sealed scoring blocks the oracle attack:
  no score feedback = no gradient to
  overfit the hidden test set.
end note

== Deadline sweep ==
L -> T : deadline reached
T -> T : run each submission in sandbox\nvs ~50 PRIVATE tests on a live v4 pool.\nScore = # PoCs that actually trigger\nthe planted vulns. Discard plaintext.
T -> C : settle(winner=A1, share=100%,\nscoresRoot) signed by enclave key
C -> A1 : pay bounty
C -->> C : emit Settled + ReputationDelta\n(A1 up, A2 zero)
C -->> R : result: 3/3 vulns found,\nattestation verifiable on-chain

@enduml
